6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 Section 1. K.S.A. 8-276 is hereby amended to read as follows: 8-276.
8 (a) In order for a person to qualify as an instructor for a driving school,
9 such person shall meet the following requirements:
10 (a)(1) Present to the department evidence of:
11 (1)(A) Credit in driver education and safety from an accredited
12 college or university equivalent to credits in those subjects required of
13 instructors in the schools accredited by the state board;
14 (2)(B) having a valid credential issued by the state board to teach
15 driver education; or
16 (3)(C) having completed at least 30 hours of classroom and 24 hours
17 of behind the wheel training under the direct supervision of an individual
18 who is presently licensed as an instructor by the state board under
19 paragraph (1) subparagraph (A) or (2) (B) and who has been continuously
20 licensed and who has actively instructed students for a period of at least
21 three years;
22 (b)(2) have knowledge of the Kansas operation lifesaver
23 highway/railroad grade crossing safety program;
24 (c)(3) be physically able to operate safely a motor vehicle and to train
25 others in the operation of motor vehicles;
26 (d)(4) provide a certificate of health from a medical doctor stating
27 that such person is physically and mentally able to safely operate a motor
28 vehicle;
29 (e)(5) except as otherwise provided in subsection (b), hold a valid
30 Kansas drivers' license; and
31 (f)(6) pay to the department an application fee of $5.
32 (b) For a motorcycle instructor subject to the provisions of this
33 section, such motorcycle instructor shall be required to:
34 (1) Have successfully completed all requirements of this section; and
35 (2) possess a valid class M driver's license or equivalent license

